            Education plays a pivotal role in disaster management. By raising
            awareness and training individuals, communities can become more
            resilient to natural disasters.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Schools should incorporate disaster preparedness into their
              curriculum.
            </li>
            <li>Community workshops can educate residents on local risks.</li>
            <li>Public campaigns can spread awareness on a larger scale.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Educated communities are better equipped to handle emergencies and
            recover quickly.
          </p>
        </article>

